00:02:28.830 --> 00:02:32.760
So first, I would like to
introduce Andre, product

00:02:32.760 --> 00:02:34.880
manager of YouTube Mobile.

00:02:34.880 --> 00:02:39.190
And then, he will talk a little
bit about the past and

00:02:39.190 --> 00:02:40.730
the present and the future
of YouTube Mobile.

00:02:40.730 --> 00:02:41.600
Thank you, Andre.

00:02:41.600 --> 00:02:42.050
ANDRE DORONIHEV:
Thanks, Jarek.

00:02:42.050 --> 00:02:43.480
JAREK WILKIEWICZ: Here you go.

00:02:43.480 --> 00:02:44.170
ANDRE DORONIHEV: Hey, guys.

00:02:44.170 --> 00:02:45.420
I wish I could land--

00:02:45.420 --> 00:02:48.370
like sky dive down
here on stage.

00:02:48.370 --> 00:02:50.680
Unfortunately, I didn't today.

00:02:50.680 --> 00:02:53.530
I lead product management for
YouTube on Mobile across our

00:02:53.530 --> 00:02:54.760
devices and mobile website.

00:02:54.760 --> 00:02:56.790
And I want to talk a little bit
about opportunities that

00:02:56.790 --> 00:02:58.900
we see in mobile videos.

00:02:58.900 --> 00:03:03.830
Now when we launched YouTube
Mobile back in 2006, it was,

00:03:03.830 --> 00:03:08.170
as many good products, it was a
toy, a toy for engineers, a

00:03:08.170 --> 00:03:09.160
baby product.

00:03:09.160 --> 00:03:10.200
Well, guess what.

00:03:10.200 --> 00:03:12.530
It has grown up a
lot since then.

00:03:12.530 --> 00:03:16.580
Today, we're streaming 600
million playbacks per day on

00:03:16.580 --> 00:03:17.480
mobile devices.

00:03:17.480 --> 00:03:18.870
Numbers are huge.

00:03:18.870 --> 00:03:22.450
Today, hundreds of millions of
phones and tablets can access

00:03:22.450 --> 00:03:24.650
full YouTube experience.

00:03:24.650 --> 00:03:27.780
And what we really see
is how the user

00:03:27.780 --> 00:03:29.830
perception is changing.

00:03:29.830 --> 00:03:33.830
So for many users today,
mobile is becoming the

00:03:33.830 --> 00:03:37.260
dominant way of accessing
YouTube.

00:03:37.260 --> 00:03:42.710
Another trend that we see is
that a lot of users see Mobile

00:03:42.710 --> 00:03:45.890
YouTube as a core feature
of their device.

00:03:45.890 --> 00:03:48.300
They just expect it to be there,
like those guys, those

00:03:48.300 --> 00:03:49.740
are my kids by the way.

00:03:49.740 --> 00:03:53.260
These guys, they just don't have
a concept of hey, this

00:03:53.260 --> 00:03:55.080
video is not on the device.

00:03:55.080 --> 00:03:58.730
For them any touch screen phone
or tablet they can grab

00:03:58.730 --> 00:04:02.050
is sort of a magical portal
that allows us to play any

00:04:02.050 --> 00:04:05.200
video they have in
mind instantly.

00:04:05.200 --> 00:04:08.180
Now, you may say these guys are
biased, and they may be.

00:04:08.180 --> 00:04:09.560
But look at our stats.

00:04:09.560 --> 00:04:12.490
As I said, 600 million playbacks
per day, but what is

00:04:12.490 --> 00:04:16.310
most fascinating is the pace
at which it is growing.

00:04:16.310 --> 00:04:19.240
3x year on year, just
in the past year.

00:04:19.240 --> 00:04:23.770
Three hours of mobile video
uploaded every single minute.

00:04:23.770 --> 00:04:27.560
So far, our goal with mobile
was just to make it work.

00:04:27.560 --> 00:04:31.270
We wanted to deliver great
consistent YouTube experience

00:04:31.270 --> 00:04:33.810
across all sorts of
mobile platforms.

00:04:33.810 --> 00:04:36.390
And the way we achieved that
was the decision we made a

00:04:36.390 --> 00:04:40.510
couple of years ago to focus on
Android application as our

00:04:40.510 --> 00:04:43.200
core experience, as the place
where we showcased new

00:04:43.200 --> 00:04:46.290
features and try out new stuff,
and then scale it

00:04:46.290 --> 00:04:50.190
across platforms via HTML5.

00:04:50.190 --> 00:04:54.030
That worked really well, and
today you can access YouTube

00:04:54.030 --> 00:04:58.160
from your Blackberry OS device
or Windows Phone or iOS

00:04:58.160 --> 00:05:02.130
Android, pretty much any modern
smartphone or tablet.

00:05:02.130 --> 00:05:04.810
Now, what's next?

00:05:04.810 --> 00:05:07.250
You know the world is changing,
and YouTube is

00:05:07.250 --> 00:05:09.450
definitely not a website
anymore.

00:05:09.450 --> 00:05:13.720
YouTube is this ecosystem of
different devices accessing

00:05:13.720 --> 00:05:16.140
the cloud of video.

00:05:16.140 --> 00:05:19.180
And it's becoming more and
more channel centric.

00:05:19.180 --> 00:05:22.930
So as you have seen already
with the site redesign on

00:05:22.930 --> 00:05:27.530
desktop, we are seeing ourselves
as the platform for

00:05:27.530 --> 00:05:31.650
the world of hundreds of
millions of channels.

00:05:31.650 --> 00:05:35.570
So what we want to achieve with
mobile going forward is

00:05:35.570 --> 00:05:39.700
to turn it into daily ritual,
this application that gives

00:05:39.700 --> 00:05:41.900
you access to all your
subscriptions

00:05:41.900 --> 00:05:43.760
wherever you are instantly.

00:05:43.760 --> 00:05:47.100
So let's say you have 10 minutes
to spare on the bus,

00:05:47.100 --> 00:05:50.410
you could just grab your phone,
open your field of

00:05:50.410 --> 00:05:54.130
subscription updates, and
instantly watch whatever you

00:05:54.130 --> 00:05:55.510
want to watch.

00:05:55.510 --> 00:05:58.190
Now, it will take us some
work to get there.

00:05:58.190 --> 00:06:00.960
We're quite not there yet.

00:06:00.960 --> 00:06:03.120
And here's our strategy, how
we want to get there.

00:06:03.120 --> 00:06:04.630
First of all, we need to
improve consumption

00:06:04.630 --> 00:06:05.950
experience a lot.

00:06:05.950 --> 00:06:07.510
We acknowledge that.

00:06:07.510 --> 00:06:10.230
Second of all, monetization
is very important to bring

00:06:10.230 --> 00:06:11.560
content to mobile.

00:06:11.560 --> 00:06:13.840
We need to make sure that
content creators have

00:06:13.840 --> 00:06:17.110
incentive to shift the usage
from desktop to mobile.

00:06:17.110 --> 00:06:20.500
Otherwise, they wouldn't just
enable videos for mobile

00:06:20.500 --> 00:06:22.030
consumption.

00:06:22.030 --> 00:06:25.290
And finally, well, you know how
they say today you cannot

00:06:25.290 --> 00:06:30.195
spell capitalism without API
in it, so opening up the

00:06:30.195 --> 00:06:31.900
ecosystem is very important.

00:06:31.900 --> 00:06:36.440
Now, let me talk about
detail consumption.

00:06:36.440 --> 00:06:39.910
I'm not sure if you noticed yet
today, we launched the new

00:06:39.910 --> 00:06:43.360
YouTube application for Android,
which is bigger than

00:06:43.360 --> 00:06:46.680
just another update, because
it's really showcasing our

00:06:46.680 --> 00:06:50.800
vision of future consumption
in the future.

00:06:50.800 --> 00:06:53.340
First feature that we launched
is the new UI

00:06:53.340 --> 00:06:54.660
focused around channels.

00:06:54.660 --> 00:06:57.080
We call it the guide.

00:06:57.080 --> 00:07:00.040
When you launch the app, you
instantly get access to all

00:07:00.040 --> 00:07:01.790
updates from your channels.

00:07:01.790 --> 00:07:04.360
And if you have a specific
channel in mind, like you want

00:07:04.360 --> 00:07:05.940
to check out the latest
[INAUDIBLE]

00:07:05.940 --> 00:07:10.300
for example, you can very easily
swipe the UI to the

00:07:10.300 --> 00:07:13.980
right and pick a particular
channel you care about.

00:07:13.980 --> 00:07:17.470
OK, you have all this great
video surfaced for you, but

00:07:17.470 --> 00:07:19.460
you know how it happens.

00:07:19.460 --> 00:07:20.730
You're on the bus.

00:07:20.730 --> 00:07:21.990
You have all this
great content.

00:07:21.990 --> 00:07:24.070
You know there's something
really cool there.

00:07:24.070 --> 00:07:24.960
You try to watch it.

00:07:24.960 --> 00:07:26.740
The connection is very slow.

00:07:26.740 --> 00:07:27.740
And it's just a pain.

00:07:27.740 --> 00:07:30.760
Instead of watching the video,
you're watching the spinner.

00:07:30.760 --> 00:07:34.990
And this is unfortunately true
despite all the recent

00:07:34.990 --> 00:07:37.060
improvements on mobile networks,
because it really

00:07:37.060 --> 00:07:39.040
depends on many factors.

00:07:39.040 --> 00:07:40.300
Like right now, in [INAUDIBLE]

00:07:40.300 --> 00:07:43.130
there are so many mobile
devices, the network is just

00:07:43.130 --> 00:07:44.920
overloaded.

00:07:44.920 --> 00:07:47.290
So the second feature we're
introducing today with this

00:07:47.290 --> 00:07:51.070
new application we call Wi-Fi
preloading, and it's quite

00:07:51.070 --> 00:07:53.660
revolutionary in its way.

00:07:53.660 --> 00:07:58.525
What happens is any time your
phone is on Wi-Fi and charger

00:07:58.525 --> 00:08:02.540
we will predownload video
content into it and store it

00:08:02.540 --> 00:08:04.400
securely on the device.

00:08:04.400 --> 00:08:07.130
So that next morning, for
example, you were on charger

00:08:07.130 --> 00:08:08.940
and Wi-Fi overnight.

00:08:08.940 --> 00:08:09.930
You wake up in the morning.

00:08:09.930 --> 00:08:13.160
You get on the shuttle,
commuting to the office, and

00:08:13.160 --> 00:08:14.150
you have flaky connection.

00:08:14.150 --> 00:08:15.430
You go through tunnels,
and so forth.

00:08:15.430 --> 00:08:19.070
But the video's already there,
so you enjoy flawless HD

00:08:19.070 --> 00:08:23.720
quality playback in your phone,
and this is really a

00:08:23.720 --> 00:08:27.730
great way to improve your
experience on the go.

00:08:27.730 --> 00:08:32.950
But now, we also acknowledge
that mobile devices are not

00:08:32.950 --> 00:08:34.929
only used on the go.

00:08:34.929 --> 00:08:38.309
Truth is, the gesture UI is so
convenient, the touch UI is so

00:08:38.309 --> 00:08:40.929
convenient, that many times
you find yourself like

00:08:40.929 --> 00:08:44.159
chilling out on the sofa, and
instead of standing up and

00:08:44.159 --> 00:08:48.455
turning on your laptop, you'll
grab your phone and explore

00:08:48.455 --> 00:08:49.900
YouTube on it.

00:08:49.900 --> 00:08:53.650
Now, touch screen is very good
for exploring and engaging

00:08:53.650 --> 00:08:56.860
with videos, but video itself
was created to be watched on a

00:08:56.860 --> 00:08:58.220
big screen TV.

00:08:58.220 --> 00:09:00.620
So the third feature we'll
launch in this

00:09:00.620 --> 00:09:03.420
new UI is Play On.

00:09:03.420 --> 00:09:07.610
This allows you to connect, to
pair your phone with the TV in

00:09:07.610 --> 00:09:11.620
the room or a smart TV in your
room, or like a TiVo box, or a

00:09:11.620 --> 00:09:15.270
Nexus Q that was presented
today.

00:09:15.270 --> 00:09:20.380
And this way, you can take
best of both worlds.

00:09:20.380 --> 00:09:23.930
You're using the UI on the phone
to navigate the side and

00:09:23.930 --> 00:09:25.220
pick the video to watch.

00:09:25.220 --> 00:09:29.430
And you're using the big
screen TV to play it.

00:09:29.430 --> 00:09:33.790
Now the best thing is that
unlike mirroring technologies,

00:09:33.790 --> 00:09:36.750
here everything's happening
through the cloud.

00:09:36.750 --> 00:09:40.150
So while your TV is playing the
video, you can continue

00:09:40.150 --> 00:09:42.330
exploring YouTube
with your phone.

00:09:42.330 --> 00:09:44.590
Or you can just leave the
YouTube app and keep it

00:09:44.590 --> 00:09:45.690
playing there.

00:09:45.690 --> 00:09:49.960
Now to recap, the way we see
consumption in the future--

00:09:49.960 --> 00:09:52.530
three things, it's
channel centric.

00:09:52.530 --> 00:09:55.950
It's optimized for streaming
on the go, and it makes

00:09:55.950 --> 00:09:59.240
devices in the living room work
together in a way that

00:09:59.240 --> 00:10:01.440
makes sense.

00:10:01.440 --> 00:10:03.510
Now switching the gears, the
second pillar of our strategy,

00:10:03.510 --> 00:10:05.650
as I said, is monetization.

00:10:05.650 --> 00:10:09.120
And it is important, because
giving great monetization

00:10:09.120 --> 00:10:12.790
options to our content creators,
we're unlocking

00:10:12.790 --> 00:10:15.280
content on YouTube on mobile.

00:10:15.280 --> 00:10:19.850
And this is a very common
problem with many devices

00:10:19.850 --> 00:10:22.830
today when you cannot play some
of the videos because

00:10:22.830 --> 00:10:25.420
content creators just didn't
feel like enabling them.

00:10:25.420 --> 00:10:28.250
We want to make sure that they
have incentive and they have

00:10:28.250 --> 00:10:32.750
great options to enable their
content for devices.

00:10:32.750 --> 00:10:37.430
Now, for advertisers mobile ads
on YouTube are actually

00:10:37.430 --> 00:10:40.190
quite cool, because unlike many
other properties that

00:10:40.190 --> 00:10:42.820
struggle with mobile
monetization, in the case of

00:10:42.820 --> 00:10:47.100
YouTube the video ad format is
very well understood, and it

00:10:47.100 --> 00:10:48.460
brings a lot of value
to advertisers.

00:10:48.460 --> 00:10:50.960
So they're willing to
pay more for it.

00:10:50.960 --> 00:10:54.940
Finally, by introducing
skippable formats, we're

00:10:54.940 --> 00:10:58.670
giving users the choice to
only watch relevant ad

00:10:58.670 --> 00:11:02.470
content, which is also
quite great.

00:11:02.470 --> 00:11:04.030
And finally, as I said,
third pillar of our

00:11:04.030 --> 00:11:06.350
strategy is you guys.

00:11:06.350 --> 00:11:10.510
We've seen a lot of success with
mobile video recently,

00:11:10.510 --> 00:11:13.350
and we really want to
share it with you.

00:11:13.350 --> 00:11:16.510
Well, of course, we don't want
you to use the API to build

00:11:16.510 --> 00:11:21.060
clones of YouTube application,
or do things that are

00:11:21.060 --> 00:11:23.860
prohibited by our policy, like
downloading content.

00:11:23.860 --> 00:11:30.250
But we see it as an opportunity
to explore new use

00:11:30.250 --> 00:11:34.080
cases around embedding videos
into existing products or

00:11:34.080 --> 00:11:37.700
building video centric
applications, like apps for

00:11:37.700 --> 00:11:40.260
content creation, curation,
or different ways

00:11:40.260 --> 00:11:42.740
of discovering videos.

00:11:42.740 --> 00:11:49.680
So to sum up, mobile video had
seen a lot of success, and

00:11:49.680 --> 00:11:51.430
it's growing really
fast right now.

00:11:51.430 --> 00:11:53.700
But the ecosystem is
in the very early

00:11:53.700 --> 00:11:55.910
stage, its very beginning.

00:11:55.910 --> 00:11:58.160
There is a lot of opportunity
with mobile video, and we

00:11:58.160 --> 00:12:01.650
really hope that you guys will
take it to new heights.

00:12:01.650 --> 00:12:02.900
Thank you.

00:12:04.976 --> 00:12:06.226
JAREK WILKIEWICZ: Thanks.

00:12:08.330 --> 00:12:09.810
Thanks, Andre.

00:12:09.810 --> 00:12:10.330
All right.

00:12:10.330 --> 00:12:14.410
So now, first of all, quick
question for you guys.

00:12:14.410 --> 00:12:17.022
Who in the room has
used YouTube APIs?

00:12:17.022 --> 00:12:19.990
Oh wow.

00:12:19.990 --> 00:12:20.670
Great.

00:12:20.670 --> 00:12:22.190
So you don't really need this.

00:12:22.190 --> 00:12:24.550
For those of you that haven't,
a quick refresher.

00:12:24.550 --> 00:12:28.210
We have two sets of APIs, data
APIs and player APIs.

00:12:28.210 --> 00:12:30.310
Data APIs allow you to integrate
with our back end,

00:12:30.310 --> 00:12:33.020
so pretty much everything you
can do on YouTube.com you can

00:12:33.020 --> 00:12:34.960
do programmatically in
your application.

00:12:34.960 --> 00:12:36.830
Player APIs allow
you to customize

00:12:36.830 --> 00:12:38.880
the playback behavior.

00:12:38.880 --> 00:12:44.930
And going back to our topic of
this talk, we will transition

00:12:44.930 --> 00:12:49.030
